How to Read This Table:
  • Long Spread: Bought V, Sold MA (betting spread will increase)
  • Short Spread: Sold V, Bought MA (betting spread will decrease)
  • Entry/Exit Z: Z-score at trade entry and exit (entry should be beyond threshold, exit near 0)
  • üõë Stop-Loss: Trade was exited due to stop-loss trigger (z-score exceeded stop-loss threshold)

Strategy Explanation

How the Pairs Trading Strategy Works:
  1. Calculate the Spread: The price difference between V and MA, adjusted by the hedge ratio.
  2. Identify Deviation: When the spread moves more than 2.0 standard deviations from its mean, a trading opportunity exists.
  3. Enter Position: Go long the spread when it's too low (buy V, sell MA), go short when it's too high.
  4. Exit Position: Close the trade when the spread returns to its mean.

Strategy Parameters Used

Lookback Period120 days
Entry Threshold2.0 standard deviations
Exit ThresholdMean (0 standard deviations)
Stop-Loss Threshold3.5 standard deviations
Initial Capital$100,000
Position Size per Leg$50,000
Fee ModelIBKR Realistic (commission + SEC + FINRA + spread)
